times the ball is expected to be red or blue.\n\nt Mick picks 2 of the 12 balls at random, without replacement.\n\nCalculate the probability that the balls are different colours.\n\nt Marie picks balls at random, without replacement, from the 12 balls.\n\nWhen she picks a green ball she stops.\n\nThe probability that she picks a green ball on pick $n$ is $\\displaystyle\\frac{21}{220}$.\n\nFind the value of $n$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"}]